collections.name: X-Y-Z by Andreas Gysin
collections.description:
Andreas Gysin’s X-Y-Z explores the built-in typeface of vintage HP X-Y vector displays like the HP1345 and HP1349, optimized for efficient rendering with minimal memory. An infinite, ever-evolving sequence of planes, defined by simple geometric shapes, flows towards the viewport. Letters and numbers appear within and around these planes, forming new structures and geometries that continuously change over time. Meaning is conveyed not through words or text, but through movement and form.

Commissioned by Flamingo DAO.

collections.name: Conclusive Oedipus by Costas Tsoclis
collections.description:
Conclusive Oedipus encompasses 297 unique digital collectibles (NFTs). Each collectible is a distinctive excerpt of up to 5 seconds, inspired by the original Conclusive Oedipus video installation created by Costas Tsoclis. Additionally, a distinct series of collectibles features 13 long movies, each a few minutes long, that narrate the entire Conclusive Oedipus artwork, and they are issued in a limited number of copies (up to 6).

The original Conclusive Oedipus video installation from 2006 featured a projection on thirteen acrylic paintings, each one 210x280 cm, creating a visual spectacle. In 2023-24, Tsoclis set up a new installation for the creation of original, unique, digital works that make up the Conclusive Oedipus NFT collection.

NFTs carry a license to specific uses of Costas Tsoclis artistic works for non-commercial purposes. Full license terms at https://nelum.art/nelum-sales-license-terms/. Extra uses require Nelum’s permission.
